-Use a hash array to store last seen index
-Create an array hash[256] and initialize all values to -1
-This helps track the last occurrence of each character
-Maintain a sliding window
-Use two pointers:
-left → start of current substring
-right → end of current substring
-Expand the window
-Iterate right from 0 to n-1
-For each character ch = s.charAt(right)
-Handle repeating characters
-If ch was seen before (hash[ch] != -1) and lies inside current window (hash[ch] >= left)
-Move left to hash[ch] + 1 to avoid repetition
-Update maximum length
-Calculate current window length: (right - left + 1)
-Update max if this length is larger
-Update last seen index
-Set hash[ch] = right
-Return result
-After traversal, return max

